# The Frontend Casebook

> Interactive frontend engineering case studies — scroll-format lessons with broken/fixed demos, junior-to-staff tone switcher, and Casey the AI guide.

## About

The Frontend Casebook at {{ site.url }} is an interactive learning site for frontend and UI engineers. Each case study is a real-world scenario written by Animesh Pandey ({{ site.author.url }}) — a senior frontend engineer. Cases cover JavaScript, CSS, performance, accessibility, React, browser APIs, and agentic UI engineering.

A companion named Casey (a kitten) guides users through each case at their chosen depth: junior, mid-level, or staff engineer.

